{
  "stem": "13395.7",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My family was well-to-do, and they didn't have need to leave.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when they wanted to leave, it was too late.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother went as far as writing to President Truman and telling him that because my father had not survived and he was a German citizen being born in Breslau, we are now penalized because we are now categorized as Polish citizens.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because when I was born, my sister was born, we were Polish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But if my father would have survived, we would have been Germans, and we would have been put on a German quota.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, we never heard from Truman.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But she tried.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She always tried.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We still thought maybe my father survived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We thought maybe he had typhoid fever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Maybe he had amnesia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Maybe somebody hit him over the head and he doesn't know who he was. 50 Years I was looking for my father.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Never give up when you don't bury your loved one.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You can't believe he's dead.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Even last November in 1995, I was going to the Elie Wiesel dinner in New York.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I was honored with other survivors.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And there was a name and a picture of a man, and underneath it says, Camp Oberlangen, [?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Bilau. ?] I immediately called the Israel bond office, got his name, and called him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I got together with him in New York, hoping that he'll tell me what happened to my father.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I'm still looking for people who'll tell me if he's really dead.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I will always be searching.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1949, my sister was already in Israel because she went with the exodus to then-Palestine.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
